java.util.EventListener
public interface MaximalCliqueFinderEventListener<V extends Vertex>
extends java.util.EventListener

This interface defines listener methods for events that transpire while finding maximal cliques in a graph.

Version:
Feb 14, 2010

Method Detail

stepCompleted

void stepCompleted(long numStepsCompleted,
                   long expectedTotalSteps)
Implementations of MaximalCliqueFinder must signal this event upon completing a logical step in their top-level algorithm. The meaning of "logical step" can vary greatly according to the underlying algorithm. This type of event is signaled to accommodate any clean up activities that may need to be performed as appropriate to the Graph implementation V. For example, if the Graph is backed by a Hibernate data source, it may be necessary to periodically flush and clear the first-level cache.

Parameters:
numStepsCompleted -
expectedTotalSteps -

cliqueFound

void cliqueFound(java.util.Set<V> clique)
This listener method handles the discovery of a new clique in the Graph. Note that this event should only be signaled for discovered cliques that meet the minCliqueSize threshold argument of the related (Graph, int) invocation.
